ase. Vanguard was informed that the family have reached out to the friends of the victim and other relations to raise at least N3million “We believe if we can increase the ransom to N3 million, the kidnappers would release our son,” a family source told Vanguard. Vanguard News Nigeria. Abductors of Ebunoluwa, the wife of Venerable Ayodeji Fagbemi, General Secretary, Church of Nigeria, Anglican Communion, are reportedly demanding N20 million ransom. December 15, 2016 In "News" Akure—AS anxiety envelopes Ondo State over the spate of kidnapping, a ransom of N100 million was yesterday demanded for the release of three civil servants abducted weekend. December 18, 2018 In "Crime Guard" The kidnapped teacher, Mr. Festus Oke, may return home afterwards, as his abductors have demanded a ransom of N20 million for his release. March 24, 2017 In "News"